Package org.fusesource.lmdbjni

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BufferCursor
    Cursor mode that allow for zero-copy lookup, navigation and modification by using addresses provided by LMDB instead of copying data for each operation.
    ByteString  
    Constants
    Mostly flags and options used throughout the API.
    Cursor
    A cursor handle.
    Database
    A database handle.
    DirectBuffer
    Supports regular, byte ordered, and atomic (memory ordered) access to an underlying buffer.
    Entry
    Key and value.
    EntryIterator
    Iterator for entries that follow the same semantics as Cursors with regards to read and write transactions and how they are closed.
    Env
    An environment handle.
    EnvInfo
    Information about the LMDB environment.
    Stat
    Statistics about the LMDB environment.
    Transaction
    A transaction handle.
